race.comment: HERAULT (11) landed the knockout blow last start at Bunbury, scoring in a photo finish over the 1675m journey. Now out to 2000m for the first time, but it looks to suit on what we've seen recently. He looks an exciting gelding on the way up and he can continue his winning run in this suitable event. MONTY ZOOMER (9) bounced back last time out when back in trip, finishing 0.5L from the winner. The 3kg of Riordan is a big tick and he has the speed to cross from a tricky barrier. Can dictate from the front and be tough to run down out to this trip for the first time. ALMAYA (3) has gone to a new level his past couple and stretching out in trip again looks ideal. Brad Parnham sticks with him and he should get every chance from the barrier. Can get back to winning ways. ROCK IN WONDER (2) can find the front and be hard to run down if he gets it all his own way. I'M NIPOTE (1) is better than he showed last start and can bounce back.
